  "text": "Remark 3. The proof of this lemma is similar to the argument in the beginning part of ( [CITATION_1] , Section 5) where Mabuchi proved semi-stability of varieties with constant scalar curvature metrics. Roughly speaking, here we consider geodesic segment connecting H * k and H k in H k , while Mabuchi ( [CITATION_2] , Section 5) considered geodesic ray in H k defined by a test configuration. The estimates in Proposition 2 show that, to prove the semi-stability as in Mabuchi's argument ( [CITATION_3] , Section 5), we only need Bergman metrics of h ∞ instead of Mabuchi's T-balanced metrics. Lemma 4. There exists a constant C > 0, which only depends on h ∞ , such that",
